&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Recognized as the No. 1 site trusted by real estate professionals, Realtor.com® has been at the forefront of online real estate for over 25 years, connecting buyers, sellers, and renters with trusted insights and expert guidance to find their perfect home. Through its robust suite of tools, Realtor.com® not only makes a significant impact on the real estate industry at large, but for consumers, navigating the biggest purchase they will make in their life, by providing a user experience that is easy to use, easy to understand, and most of all, easy to make decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us on our mission to empower more people to find their way home by breaking barriers to entry, making the right connections, and building confidence through expert guidance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Scientist Intern - Master&#39;s Level&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with stakeholders across the Data Science and Analytics organization at &lt;a href=&quot;http://realtor.com/&quot;&gt;Realtor.com&lt;/a&gt; to identify business problems and opportunities where data science can add value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize advanced statistical learning and mathematical techniques to drive insights and translate them into strategic recommendations for stakeholders in the Finance and Revenue organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and guide the team in designing experiments, conducting A/B tests, and performing statistical analysis to drive actionable insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development and maintenance of data pipelines, data integration, and data visualization tools to streamline the data science workflow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Machine Learning Engineering teams to collectively enhance business processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate with an aptitude to quickly learn new and emerging technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter willing to jump into difficult situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insanely curious, analytical, and loves solving problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agile, adaptable, and able to obtain results from cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal, written, and presentation communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand data life cycle and lineage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to translate business needs to insights from the data into a compelling story&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in an accredited 4-year College or University, pursuing a Masters Degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Engineering, or related degrees or related concentrations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience in one or more of the following: SQL*,* Python, dbt, Airflow, R, Tableau, or other data tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a graduation date between December 2026 and June 2027&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to complete the full internship lasting eleven weeks between Monday, June 1, 2026, through Friday, August 14, 2026&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work well in a team setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate a positive attitude, professionalism, attention to detail, and a strong worth ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Desire to embrace new challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience dealing with multiple competing priorities and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt; Our Internship Program is based in Austin, TX, and follows a hybrid schedule (three days on-site, two days remote). &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visa sponsorship and relocation assistance are not available for this program.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Make Your Mark at Realtor.com®&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;You only get one first internship, so make it count. At Realtor.com®, you’ll do more than gain experience—you’ll make an impact, grow your network, and help us build a better future for home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to build a way home for everyone? Apply and join us in Summer 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Do the best work of your life at Realtor.com®&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here, you’ll partner with a diverse team of experts as you use leading-edge tech to empower everyone to meet a crucial goal: finding their way home. And you’ll find your way home too. At Realtor.com®, you’ll bring your full self to work as you innovate with speed, serve our consumers, and champion your teammates. In return, we’ll provide you with a warm, welcoming, and inclusive culture; intellectual challenges; and the development opportunities you need to grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity is important to us, therefore, Realtor.com® is an Equal Opportunity Employer regardless of age, color, national origin, race, religion, creed, gender, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, marital status, status as a disabled veteran and/or veteran of the Vietnam Era or any other characteristic protected by federal, state or local law. In addition, Realtor.com® will provide reasonable accommodations for otherwise qualified disabled individuals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
